---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="GTA 6 Guide Domain Strategy" description="Brand-first domain recommendations for a GTA 6 guide site that avoids official-looking trademark confusion.">
  <header class="page-header shell">
    <div class="page-kicker">Domain strategy</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Domain Recommendations</h1>
    <p class="page-intro">
      Search demand includes GTA 6 guide, map, wiki, cheats, missions, cars, locations, release date, and preorder.
      The domain should not try to look official. Put search terms in page titles, not in a confusing brand identity.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="section-tight shell split">
    <div class="panel">
      <h2>Recommended Direction</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>leonidaledger.com</strong> - best match to the current brand and source-led concept.</li>
        <li><strong>openworldfieldguide.com</strong> - broader and safer if the site expands beyond GTA 6.</li>
        <li><strong>launchgameguide.com</strong> - strong for release/preorder/search intent, less distinctive.</li>
        <li><strong>vicecityfieldguide.com</strong> - memorable, but closer to in-game naming than the first two.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <h2>Avoid</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Official-looking names that combine GTA, Rockstar, store, preorder, or wiki in the core domain.</li>
        <li>Any logo or favicon that imitates Rockstar, Take-Two, or Grand Theft Auto branding.</li>
        <li>Domains that imply endorsement, early access, preorder selling, or direct publisher affiliation.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

